    "body": "This is my proposed solution to solving https://github.com/spack/spack/issues/7441 .\r\n\r\nIn summary, when using `spack bootstrap` and then `setup-env.sh`, the code currently used to populate `SPACK_SHELL` can resolve to a different process than the shell, for example if you source `setup-env.sh` from a script, then `SPACK_SHELL` will be the name of the script, causing problems.",
